 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dyrauelene>Dyrauelene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 107<br> <font color=#333333>(11/27/02 8:19:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7989.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Possible fix</span><hr size=1> I work as tech support for cable modems.  Cable modems + wireless routers = problems.<br>
<br>
Well, they -can-.  I highly recommend moving the router as far from the modem as humanly possible... a minimum of 6 feet or more.  The signals from wireless routers can actually interfere (so my tier 3 tells me) with the modem and / or the RF signal in the line.<br>
<br>
Hope that helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kalamos>Kalamos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 446<br> <font color=#333333>(11/27/02 9:58:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7989.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Possible fix</span><hr size=1> Yeah LD problems with Linksys Routers generally has alot to do with the firmware version you are running in my experience.  It helps to open ports in the port triggering section of your router software.<br>
<br>
Do a search on the Everquest tech help board for the user Turtoni.  He has made some excellent posts about Linksys routers, and claims to run a Linksys Wireless Router flawlessly with EQ.<br>
